jacdac.AirQualityIndexReg.AqiIndex:
Read-only AQI u16.16 (uint32_t). Air quality index, typically refreshed every second.
* ```
const [aqiIndex] = jdunpack<[number]>(buf, "u16.16")
```
jacdac.AirQualityIndexReg.AqiIndexError:
Read-only AQI u16.16 (uint32_t). Error on the AQI measure.
* ```
const [aqiIndexError] = jdunpack<[number]>(buf, "u16.16")
```
jacdac.AirQualityIndexReg.MaxAqiIndex:
Constant AQI u16.16 (uint32_t). Maximum AQI reading, representing a very poor air quality.
* ```
const [maxAqiIndex] = jdunpack<[number]>(buf, "u16.16")
```
jacdac.AirQualityIndexReg.MinAqiIndex:
Constant AQI u16.16 (uint32_t). Minimum AQI reading, representing a good air quality. Typically 0.
* ```
const [minAqiIndex] = jdunpack<[number]>(buf, "u16.16")
```
modules.AirQualityIndexClient:
The Air Quality Index is a measure of how clean or polluted air is. From min, good quality, to high, low quality.
The range of AQI may vary between countries (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_quality_index).
modules.AirQualityIndexClient.aqiIndex: Air quality index, typically refreshed every second.
modules.AirQualityIndexClient.maxAqiInde: Maximum AQI reading, representing a very poor air quality.
modules.AirQualityIndexClient.minAqiInde: Minimum AQI reading, representing a good air quality. Typically 0.
modules.AirQualityIndexClient.onAqiIndex: Run code when the aqi index changes by the given threshold value.
